<D>__{yo! up here!}
<A>__{blair williams, the helmeted pilot who ejected, hangs from the tangled remains of her parachute, caught in the trees about fifteen feet in the air above marcus. marcus moves closer. blair struggles to saw through her lines with a knife.}
<C>__{blair }
<D>__{who are you }
<A>__{the lines suddenly snap, blair falls from the tree. marcus' reflexes are fast as ever, he's beneath her in an instant and catches her. he holds her in his arms:}
<C>__{marcus}
<D>__{name's marcus.}
<C>__{blair}
<D>__{you can put me down now, marcus.}
<A>__{he does so. blair pulls off her helmet, her hair is short. she's in her 20s, pretty, petite but strong, a no nonsense, battle hardened member of the resistance. she pulls a compass from her flight suit, consults it briefly as she orients herself.}
<C>__{blair }
<D>__{i've got an elt, but i can't call for a rescue here. there's an outpost a few miles upriver not my favorite people in the world, but it's safe. let's move.}
<A>__{blair is already moving, marcus hesitates, then points across the water.}
<C>__{marcus}
<D>__{i'm heading that way.}
<C>__{blair}
<P>__{(a short laugh)}
<D>__{the hot zone? no you're not.}
